      • generateRandomPrimeBigInteger

        public static java.math.BigInteger generateRandomPrimeBigInteger(int bitLength,
                                                                 int certainty,
                                                                 java.util.Random rnd)
        Generates a random prime BigInteger with a specified bit-length and a given certainty. The certainty determines the accuracy of the primality check and is used as follows: probability of accuracy = 100 * (1 - 1/(2^certainty)) For example, if certainty=4, then probability of accuracy = 100 * (1 - 1/16) = 93.75% If certainty=100, then probability of accuracy = 100 * (1 - 1/2^100) = 99.99999999.....%
        Parameters:
        bitLength - the length of the requested BigInteger in bits
        certainty - the given certainty
        rnd - the given random generator object
        Returns:
        a random prime BigInteger

        Parameters:

        b - the second number
        Returns:
        the gcd(a, b)
